sorry, handbone.

11:30.389 --> 11:32.123
[ high-pitched ]
you're a mess.

11:35.095 --> 11:39.330
<i>So, operation swag back</i>
<i>was in full effect.</i>

11:39.332 --> 11:41.099
<i>I was planning my big party,</i>

11:41.101 --> 11:43.702
<i>And it was testing</i>
<i>off the charts.</i>

11:43.704 --> 11:45.003
Ooh, this is crazy!

11:45.005 --> 11:48.373
So, when everybody's leaving,
they'll get a thumb drive

11:48.375 --> 11:51.076
Of all 40 tracks
that they just partay'd to

11:51.078 --> 11:54.913
At the 40th birthday partay
to end all partays!

11:54.915 --> 11:57.415
Oh, hoo! Oh, man!

11:57.417 --> 11:59.017
You ain't giving them
a chance, dre!

11:59.019 --> 12:00.018
I'm killing 'em.

12:00.020 --> 12:01.252
Vis-ion-ary.

12:01.254 --> 12:02.854
That's what they call me.

12:02.856 --> 12:04.789
[ laughs ]
you hear that, curtis?

12:04.791 --> 12:06.991
Everyone's gonna get
a thumb drive

12:06.993 --> 12:09.294
With the music
from the partay.

12:09.296 --> 12:11.029
[ laughs ]
that's hilarious, man.

12:11.031 --> 12:13.298
Can you imagine
somebody actually doing that?

12:13.300 --> 12:15.266
[ laughs ]
huh?

12:17.103 --> 12:18.136
Oh, that's actually
happening?

12:18.138 --> 12:22.173
That's -- that's probably gonna
be tight, boss man. Yep.

12:22.175 --> 12:23.742
Damn right
it's gonna be tight.

12:23.744 --> 12:25.477
I throw a fly party.
You'll see.

12:25.479 --> 12:26.911
You got to come through.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.346
I-I got to come through?

12:28.348 --> 12:30.882
Is that like
a mandatory work thing or...?

12:30.884 --> 12:32.450
You kn-- you know what?
It's cool.

12:32.452 --> 12:33.885
I'm sure
it'll be done early enough

12:33.887 --> 12:35.420
For me to do something fun
afterwards.

12:35.422 --> 12:36.921
What --
[ clears throat ]

12:36.923 --> 12:40.024
Uh, what you talking about
hitting later?

12:40.026 --> 12:44.028
'cause I'll probably do a lap
at dude's thing and then bounce.

12:44.030 --> 12:45.330
Charlie.

12:45.332 --> 12:47.832
You literally just called me
a visionary.

12:47.834 --> 12:49.100
[ chuckles nervously ]

12:49.903 --> 12:52.303
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no. Hold on.

12:52.305 --> 12:54.539
You really think
my party's gonna be whack?

12:54.541 --> 12:57.542
All right, look,
to be honest with you...

12:57.544 --> 12:59.444
It sounds like
a jammy jam.

12:59.446 --> 13:00.545
Damn!

13:00.547 --> 13:02.881
Jammy jam?
Okay, hold.

13:02.883 --> 13:04.015
What would you do?

13:04.017 --> 13:06.017
[ sighs ]
I don't know.

13:06.019 --> 13:08.787
Uh, maybe a rotating bullpen
of deejays.

13:08.789 --> 13:11.956
And let's talk about staff.
Smads.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.224
Smads?

13:13.226 --> 13:15.794
Singer, model,
actress, dancer. Right?

13:15.796 --> 13:18.897
<i>So, curtis went on to describe</i>
<i>an incredible party,</i>

13:18.899 --> 13:22.567
<i>And I realized</i>
<i>I had a new party planner.</i>

13:22.569 --> 13:24.068
And you put that
all together

13:24.070 --> 13:27.472
And you do it at a crazy-cool
secret hot spot,

13:27.474 --> 13:29.908
That's how you throw a party
in 2015.

13:29.910 --> 13:31.543
Wow.
Okay, I'm with that.

13:31.545 --> 13:34.879
Now,<i> he's</i> the visionary.
[ chuckles ]

13:34.881 --> 13:37.048
And you inviting me
to a jammy jam.

13:37.050 --> 13:38.550
[ scoffs ]

13:38.552 --> 13:40.351
Now, what size
are these smads?

13:40.353 --> 13:42.287
Because I like thick'ums.

13:42.289 --> 13:45.056
So, it's my husband's
40th birthday,

13:45.058 --> 13:47.492
And his favorite movie
growing up was "beastmaster."

13:47.494 --> 13:49.894
So, long story short --

13:49.896 --> 13:51.329
How much for a ferret?

13:51.331 --> 13:53.965
Uh-huh.
Dre's real gift
finally came,

13:53.967 --> 13:58.369
Something he's been wanting
since he was 16 --

13:58.371 --> 13:59.971
Motorcycle lessons.

13:59.973 --> 14:01.206
[ laughs ]

14:01.208 --> 14:02.440
Cost a fortune.

14:02.442 --> 14:05.009
But can you really
put a price

14:05.011 --> 14:07.946
On making your baby's dreams
come true?

14:07.948 --> 14:08.947
[ chuckles ]

14:08.949 --> 14:10.081
It's a lot.

14:13.219 --> 14:15.620
Okay, what about,
like, a python?

14:15.622 --> 14:17.555
O-or like
a not-that-poisonous snake?

14:17.557 --> 14:19.891
<i>So, with the party</i>
<i>fast approaching,</i>

14:19.893 --> 14:21.960
<i>I put myself in curtis' hands</i>

14:21.962 --> 14:25.930
<i>And let him turn me into</i>
<i>a swaggier version of myself.</i>

14:25.932 --> 14:30.034
Now, I got this thing with
my hat that I do like this.

14:30.036 --> 14:31.469
Oh.

14:31.471 --> 14:33.571
Okay.
Um...Really?

14:33.573 --> 14:35.106
You know,
'cause I can't see.

14:35.108 --> 14:36.608
What?
Hey, dad.

14:36.610 --> 14:38.176
Uh, for reasons
we can't share,

14:38.178 --> 14:40.111
We need you to help us
get in the attic.

14:40.113 --> 14:41.212
Okay.
Slow your roll, son.

14:41.214 --> 14:42.513
I'm getting swaggified
right now.

14:42.515 --> 14:46.551
Look, I only have a few minutes
with curtis, all right?

14:46.553 --> 14:50.588
And he's taking some valuable
time from his day to help me.

14:50.590 --> 14:52.190
Aren't you
<i>his</i> boss?

14:52.192 --> 14:54.092
Get out of here!
All right?!

14:54.094 --> 14:55.960
I'm trying
to get swaggified!

14:55.962 --> 14:59.998
Now, in the club, they like
glow sticks, glow necklaces.

15:00.000 --> 15:00.965
Right.

15:00.967 --> 15:02.300
Weak.
What?

15:02.302 --> 15:04.335
Glow mouth guard.

15:04.337 --> 15:06.437
What?!
Get out of here!

15:07.673 --> 15:09.340
[ muffled ]
oh! This is it!

15:09.342 --> 15:11.075
Okay,
get me 600 of these.

15:11.077 --> 15:12.210
Yeah!

15:12.212 --> 15:14.212
<i>So, on the evening</i>
<i>of the party,</i>

15:14.214 --> 15:16.581
<i>I wanted to do a walk-through</i>
<i>of the venue.</i>

15:16.583 --> 15:18.182
Now,
I know a lot of people

15:18.184 --> 15:20.151
Think skid row
is a little ratchet,

15:20.153 --> 15:21.386
[ siren wailing ]
but trust me...

15:21.388 --> 15:22.387
Mm-hmm.
...It's the business.

15:22.389 --> 15:26.157
T-that's what I'm looking for --
ratchet business.

15:26.159 --> 15:29.327
Like, I was just here
the other night,

15:29.329 --> 15:30.395
And it was sick!

15:30.397 --> 15:32.330
[ laughs ]

15:34.934 --> 15:36.034
What?

15:36.036 --> 15:37.568
Yo, uh...

15:37.570 --> 15:39.537
I could have swore
it was right here.

15:39.539 --> 15:40.705
What?

15:40.707 --> 15:43.274
Damn, son.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.575
What?

15:44.577 --> 15:45.610
They tore it down.

15:45.612 --> 15:47.178
They --
they tore it down?

15:47.180 --> 15:49.280
They tore it down!

15:49.282 --> 15:51.316
Tell me
that spot ain't cool.

15:51.318 --> 15:54.485
Are you hearing yourself
right now?

15:54.487 --> 15:56.988
I have 200 people coming
to my 40th birthday party,

15:56.990 --> 16:00.425
And you're telling me
I don't have a venue.
[ camera clicks ]

16:00.427 --> 16:03.494
I'm telling you
that I found a venue so cool...

16:03.496 --> 16:04.729
That it's gone.

16:06.031 --> 16:07.065
You are welcome.

16:07.067 --> 16:08.132
Oh.

16:08.134 --> 16:09.634
Uh...

16:09.636 --> 16:11.369
So, you saying no
to this?

16:11.371 --> 16:13.738
'cause this will still work,
boss!

16:13.740 --> 16:16.741
We'll get some -- we'll get some
fold-out chairs and a jumper!

16:19.478 --> 16:22.480
So, we just need
one last piece from dad,

16:22.482 --> 16:25.650
Yep, and I don't want
to sound corny,

16:25.652 --> 16:27.652
But putting this much thought
into his gift --

16:27.654 --> 16:29.320
Kind of making me love him
even more.

16:29.322 --> 16:30.755
Yeah.
Yeah.
Yeah.

16:30.757 --> 16:32.090
Bow.

16:32.092 --> 16:34.592
Not now. Okay, guys?
But we really --

16:34.594 --> 16:36.394
I said, "not now."

16:36.396 --> 16:38.229
[ scoffs ]

16:38.231 --> 16:40.298
This is what I get
for opening my heart.

16:40.300 --> 16:43.301
Babe, I can't believe curtis
messed up my whole party.

16:43.303 --> 16:44.736
And this jacket
is tight.

16:44.738 --> 16:47.305
Yeah, if you like
purple leather.

16:47.307 --> 16:48.639
No. I mean
literally tight.

16:48.641 --> 16:50.141
Like, I can barely
move my arms.

16:50.143 --> 16:52.510
You know, babe,
if you think about it,

16:52.512 --> 16:55.747
This whole party fiasco is
someone else's fault entirely.

16:55.749 --> 16:56.748
Mm-hmm.

16:56.750 --> 16:57.715
Yours.

16:57.717 --> 17:00.752
No. I'm pretty sure
it's curtis' fault.

17:00.754 --> 17:02.186
Are you sure?
Yes.

17:02.188 --> 17:04.122
'cause, you know,
the dre I fell in love with

17:04.124 --> 17:06.057
Had so much swag that
he would have trusted himself

17:06.059 --> 17:08.626
Instead of turning his party
over to some kid.

17:08.628 --> 17:10.461
Huh.

17:10.463 --> 17:11.729
Yeah, you're right.

17:11.731 --> 17:13.231
It was curtis' fault.

17:13.233 --> 17:15.600
What I need to do
is salvage this party.

17:15.602 --> 17:17.035
Okay.

17:18.604 --> 17:20.705
Nate.
What up, little man?

17:20.707 --> 17:22.607
I need six cases --
champagne.

17:22.609 --> 17:27.211
<i>With two hours to go</i>
<i>until the party</i>
whoo-hoo!

17:27.213 --> 17:29.347
<i>And no venue, no food,</i>
<i>and no music,</i>
whoo!

17:29.349 --> 17:32.116
<i>I had no choice</i>
<i>but to go old-school</i>

17:32.118 --> 17:34.786
<i>And use my contacts</i>
<i>to throw a house party.</i>

17:34.788 --> 17:39.257
<i>But for it to be a truly epic</i>
<i>dre johnson joint,</i>

17:39.259 --> 17:40.825
<i>I also had to call in a favor.</i>

17:40.827 --> 17:42.427
Yo, j.D.

17:42.429 --> 17:43.795
What's up, man?
It's dre.

17:43.797 --> 17:45.797
Yo, dre, what's up?

17:45.799 --> 17:48.666
I sold like
250 million records.

17:48.668 --> 17:51.302
Uh...Yeah. I know.

17:51.304 --> 17:53.337
Hey, hey, listen,
I need a favor, brother.

17:53.339 --> 17:54.806
Man, anything for you.

17:54.808 --> 17:56.674
I discovered bow wow.

17:56.676 --> 17:59.510
Okay. I-I don't see what that
has to do with anything.

17:59.512 --> 18:02.180
But, um, look, man,
I'm glad you can help me out.

18:02.182 --> 18:05.383
So, so def.

18:05.385 --> 18:06.384
Okay.

18:06.386 --> 18:08.553
Okay.

18:11.690 --> 18:13.724
All: Hey!
[ 50 cent's "in da club" plays ]

18:13.726 --> 18:15.426
<i>So, by the time</i>
<i>the first guests arrived,</i>

18:15.428 --> 18:16.561
<i>I'd pulled it off.</i>

18:16.563 --> 18:18.129
♪ go, shorty,
it's your birthday ♪

18:18.131 --> 18:20.131
Somebody put your hands
in the air one time!

18:20.133 --> 18:22.600
♪ we gonna party like
it's your birthday ♪
hey! Hey! Hey!

18:22.602 --> 18:23.768
<i>And it was cool.</i>

18:23.770 --> 18:25.870
You still just gonna take
that lap?

18:25.872 --> 18:27.338
Or are you gonna stay?

18:27.340 --> 18:29.373
Oh, oh, oh,
I ain't going nowhere.

18:29.375 --> 18:30.808
[ laughs ]
hey, hey, dad.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.578
So, I was wondering
if you could --

18:33.580 --> 18:36.581
Hey, boss man,
this party is bananas!

18:36.583 --> 18:37.748
Give me one second,
okay?

18:37.750 --> 18:40.751
A party at your own house?
Mm-hmm.

18:40.753 --> 18:42.120
How'd you think of that?

18:42.122 --> 18:45.256
'cause he's the best,
"new school."

18:45.258 --> 18:47.425
And stop asking me to go
to that thing with you later.

18:47.427 --> 18:48.759
I'm staying
at dude's party.

18:48.761 --> 18:49.861
[ chuckles ]

18:49.863 --> 18:51.863
Zoey: Uh, so, dad...

18:51.865 --> 18:56.467
If we could actually
show you --
jermaine:
Yo! Yo! Yo, party people!

18:56.469 --> 18:58.236
I go by the name
of jermaine dupri,

18:58.238 --> 19:00.338
And it's time
that we give a big shout-out

19:00.340 --> 19:01.472
To my man, dre johnson!

19:01.474 --> 19:02.907
♪ hang on tight ♪
[ all cheering ]

19:02.909 --> 19:03.908
What's up?

19:03.910 --> 19:05.276
What up, j.D.?

19:05.278 --> 19:06.811
Hey, give me a second,
zo-zo, okay?

19:06.813 --> 19:08.446
Happy birthday, dre.

19:08.448 --> 19:10.281
Thanks, j.D.

19:10.283 --> 19:11.616
You know
I danced for whodini, right?

19:11.618 --> 19:13.518
Uh...Yes, I did.

19:13.520 --> 19:15.219
And I'm vegan.

19:15.221 --> 19:16.687
Like, no meat.
Okay.

19:16.689 --> 19:17.788
Completely off the dairy.

19:17.790 --> 19:21.192
<i>I did it.</i>
<i>I got my swag back.</i>

19:21.194 --> 19:23.461
<i>On no notice,</i>
<i>I threw a killer party</i>

19:23.463 --> 19:24.795
<i>With the people</i>
<i>I care most about.</i>

19:24.797 --> 19:28.332
<i>Wait. Where</i> are<i> the people</i>
<i>I care most about?</i>

19:28.334 --> 19:30.434
♪ and let my mama tell it ♪

19:30.436 --> 19:31.602
Zo?

19:31.604 --> 19:33.471
Oh.
You're<i> all</i> up here.

19:33.473 --> 19:34.672
What's going on?

19:34.674 --> 19:38.676
We were all waiting up here to
show you the present we got you.

19:38.678 --> 19:40.845
Well, where<i> is</i> my present,
baby girl?

19:40.847 --> 19:42.580
No, it can wait
till after the party.

19:42.582 --> 19:43.881
Jermaine dupri's
spinning.

19:43.883 --> 19:45.783
He made
"money ain't a thing."

19:45.785 --> 19:48.486
He told me while I was waiting
behind him at the taco bar.

19:48.488 --> 19:51.956
Okay, look, look, look,
the party can wait, okay?

19:51.958 --> 19:53.724
Now, where's my gift?

19:53.726 --> 19:54.892
All right.

19:54.894 --> 19:56.460
Sit down.

19:56.462 --> 20:00.498
[ alphaville's "forever young"
plays ]

20:00.500 --> 20:01.599
Oh.

20:05.604 --> 20:08.940
♪ let's dance in style,
let's dance for a while ♪

20:08.942 --> 20:12.710
♪ heaven can wait,
we're only watching the skies ♪

20:12.712 --> 20:15.346
♪ hoping for the best
but expecting the worst ♪

20:15.348 --> 20:19.217
♪ are you gonna drop the bomb
or not? ♪

20:19.219 --> 20:22.220
♪ let us die young
or let us live forever ♪

20:22.222 --> 20:25.523
<i>I'd been so obsessed</i>
<i>with getting my swag back,</i>

20:25.525 --> 20:29.727
<i>The only people you really need</i>
<i>to have swagger for</i>

20:29.729 --> 20:32.830
<i>Are the people who don't care</i>
<i>if you have any at all.</i>

20:32.832 --> 20:35.866
♪ forever young,
I want to be forever young ♪

20:35.868 --> 20:39.237
Dre: Look at my family.

20:39.239 --> 20:41.806
♪ do you really want
to live forever? ♪

20:41.808 --> 20:42.773
Hey.

20:42.775 --> 20:44.408
♪ ...Forever... ♪

20:44.410 --> 20:45.810
I love you guys.

20:45.812 --> 20:48.446
We love you, too.

20:52.517 --> 20:54.352
The kids did
a nice job.

20:54.354 --> 20:57.655
So, what'd you end up
getting your man?

20:57.657 --> 20:58.923
Oh, nothing big.

20:58.925 --> 21:01.192
Just those four children
over there

21:01.194 --> 21:03.561
Making him cry
tears of joy.

21:03.563 --> 21:04.595
Cop-out.

21:04.597 --> 21:05.596
Oh.

21:05.598 --> 21:07.465
Also, later tonight,

21:07.467 --> 21:09.367
I plan on doing things
to your son

21:09.369 --> 21:11.502
That are gonna make it
very hard for him

21:11.504 --> 21:13.804
To ride a motorcycle
anytime soon.

21:13.806 --> 21:15.906
Girl, I don't want
to hear that!

21:15.908 --> 21:17.908
[ gasps ]
oh, no, no. Wait!
Unh-unh! Unh-unh!

21:17.910 --> 21:19.043
Wait.
That came out wrong!

21:19.045 --> 21:23.014
No,
but it came out wrong.
I don't want to think about it,
for the love of god.
